  <body>
    This java applet shows how the electromagnetic wave propagated in the 
    media.

    <ol>
      <li>
        Red segment represent Electric Field
      </li>
      <li>
        Gray segment represent Magnetic Field
      </li>
    </ol>
    You can modify:

    <ol>
      <li>
        T :period of the wave. =&gt; wavelength(lamda)=vy*T
      </li>
      <li>
        Ez: electric field magnitude
      </li>
      <li>
        vy: wave velocity. =&gt; Ez/Bx=vy, where Bx is magnetic field magnitude
      </li>
    </ol>
    Please notice that E/B field are in phase when electromagnetic is travel 
    in vacuum. For more info: <a href="http://weelookang.blogspot.sg/2011/10/ejs-open-source-propagation-of.html" cr="true">http://weelookang.blogspot.sg/2011/10/ejs-open-source-propagation-of.html</a>
  </body>
